      MaskIconOpaque	      on
      MaskIconRotate	      "none"
      MaskIconUnits	      "autoscale"
      System {
	Name			"More Info"
	Location		[71, 80, 999, 735]
	Open			off
	ModelBrowserVisibility	off
	ModelBrowserWidth	200
	ScreenColor		"white"
	PaperOrientation	"landscape"
	PaperPositionMode	"auto"
	PaperType		"usletter"
	PaperUnits		"inches"
	ZoomFactor		"100"
	AutoZoom		on
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [472, 592]
	  Text			  "Observe that during the fault the terminal "
"voltage drops to about 0.2 pu and the excitation voltage hits the  limit of 6"
" pu. After fault clearing and islanding\n the SM  mechanical power  increases"
" from its initial value of 0.16 pu to the final value of 0.80 pu required by "
"the resistive and motor load (2.49 MW) . After 3 seconds,\n the terminal volt"
"age stabilizes at 1 pu. The motor speed decreases transiently from 1789 rpm t"
"o 1624 rpm, then it recovers close to its normal value after 2 seconds.\n\nIf"
" you  increase the fault duration to 12 cycles by changing the breaker openin"
"g time to 0.3s, you will notice that the system collapses.\n The ASM speed sl"
"ows down to zero after 2 seconds.               "
	  FontName		  "Times"
	  FontSize		  12
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [40, 451]
	  Text			  "3"
	  FontSize		  14
	  FontWeight		  "bold"
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [40, 286]
	  Text			  "1"
	  FontSize		  14
	  FontWeight		  "bold"
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [69, 257]
	  Text			  "Demonstration"
	  FontSize		  14
	  FontWeight		  "bold"
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [74, 97]
	  Text			  "Circuit Description"
	  FontSize		  14
	  FontWeight		  "bold"
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [464, 37]
	  Text			  "This demonstration illustrates fault and is"
"landing of an induction motor/diesel-generator system.\nIt also demonstrates "
"the Machine Load Flow option of the PowerGUI .\n( See Tutorial Session 5)"
	  FontSize		  14
	  FontWeight		  "bold"
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [451, 180]
	  Text			  "A plant consisting of a resistive and motor"
" load (ASM) is fed at 2400 V from a distibution 25 kV network through a 6 MVA"
" 25/2.kV Wye-Delta transformer and from an\nemergency synchronous generator/ "
"diesel engine unit (SM). The 25 kV network is modelled by a simple R-L equiva"
"lent source (short-circuit level 1000 MVA) and a 5 MW load.\n The  asynchrono"
"us motor is  rated 2250 HP, 2.4 kV and the synchronous machine is rated 3.125"
" MVA, 2.4kV. The SM excitation is performed by the standard\n excitation bloc"
"k provided with Powerlib. The diesel engine and governor system are modelled "
"by a SIMULINK block (See tutorial, session 5 in the user`s manual).\nInitiall"
"y, the motor develops a mechanical power of 2000 HP (1.49 MW) and the diesel "
"generator provides 500 kW (0.16 pu) of active power.\nThe generator controls "
"the 2400V bus B2 voltage at 1pu and generates 500kW (0.16 pu) of active power"
".  At t=0.1 s, a three-phase to ground\n fault occurs on the 25 kV system, ca"
"using opening of the 25kV circuit breaker at t=0.2 s .\n\nThe demonstration i"
"llustrates the mecanical and electrical transients following the fault and is"
"landing of the Motor/Generator system."
	  FontName		  "Times"
	  FontSize		  12
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [404, 522]
	  Text			  "Open the 4  scopes displaying the terminal "
"voltge, field voltage, mechanical power and speed of the synchronous machine "
"as well as \nthe scope displaying the asynchronous motor speed. Start the sim"
"ulation."
	  FontName		  "Times"
	  FontSize		  12
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [454, 292]
	  Text			  "Start Simulation. If the SM and ASM initial"
" conditions are not properly set you  will  observe that the voltage and curr"
"ents Machine do not start in steady state.\n Stop the simulation."
	  FontName		  "Times"
	  FontSize		  12
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [40, 316]
	  Text			  "2"
	  FontSize		  14
	  FontWeight		  "bold"
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [449, 372]
	  Text			  "In order to start the simulation in steady-"
"state you must initialize the synchronous machine and the asynchronous motor "
"for the desired load flow.\nOpen the  POWERGUI and select \"Load Flow & Machi"
"ne initialization\" in the Tools menu. The machine \"Bus type\" should be alr"
"eady initialized as \"PV generator\",\n indicating that  the load flow will b"
"e performed with the machine controlling its active power and terminal voltag"
"e. Specify the desired values by entering\n the following parameters : U AB ("
"Vrms) = 2400;  P (wattts) =500e3. Specify also the ASM mechanical power by en"
"tering Pmec (Watts)= 2000*746.\n Then press the \"Execute Load Flow\" button"
"\n.\n Once the load flow is solved the phasors of AB and BC machine voltages "
"and currents flowing in phases A and B are updated.\n The SM reactive power, "
" mechanical power and  field voltage are displayed : Q =315 kvar; Pmec=500 kW"
" (0.1601 pu) ; field voltage Ef=1.182 pu;\n The active and reactive powers ab"
"sorbed by the motor,  slip and torque are also displayed.  "
	  FontName		  "Times"
	  FontSize		  12
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [469, 467]
	  Text			  "As the diesel engine governor and SM excita"
"tion system contain several states, they should also be initialized according"
" to the values calculated by the load flow.\n Open the GOVERNOR block in the "
"Diesel Engine subsystem. The initial mechanical power has been set to 0.1601 "
"pu in the GOVERNOR. \nNow open the EXCITATION block. The initial terminal vol"
"tage and field voltage have been set respectively to 1.0 and 1.182 pu."
	  FontName		  "Times"
	  FontSize		  12
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [40, 516]
	  Text			  "4"
	  FontSize		  14
	  FontWeight		  "bold"
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [471, 221]
	  Text			  " "
	  FontName		  "Times"
	  FontSize		  12
	}
	Annotation {
	  Position		  [463, 73]
	  Text			  "G. Sybille ; Hydro-Quebec (IREQ)"
	}
      }
    }
